## 📌 What is CivicConnect?

CivicConnect is a full-stack MERN application that lets registered citizens report local civic issues — potholes, broken streetlights, overflowing drains — and rally their community to upvote them. The more upvotes an issue gets, the higher its priority climbs automatically. If authorities don't act within a set time window, the issue auto-escalates up a 3-tier admin hierarchy (Ward → District → City), ensuring no report gets buried.

### The problem it solves

Traditional civic complaint systems are black boxes — you file a complaint and never hear back. CivicConnect makes the entire pipeline transparent: every status change, every escalation, every assignment is visible to the public in real time.

---

## ✨ Features

### For Citizens
- 🔐 **Verified accounts only** — sign up with ward/district to route reports correctly, no anonymous spam
- 📍 **Rich issue reporting** — 15 categories, manual address + interactive map pin, photo/video uploads
- 👍 **Community upvoting** — upvote issues you care about (cannot upvote your own)
- 📊 **Auto priority upgrade by votes** — 10 votes → Medium · 25 → High · 50 → Critical
- 🔺 **Full escalation history** — see exactly when and why an issue moved up the chain
- 🗺️ **Live map view** — all issues pinned on an interactive map with colour-coded markers
- 🔥 **Hot / New / Critical sort** — surface the most urgent issues instantly

### For Admins — 3-tier hierarchy

| Level | Role | Can act on | Extra powers |
|-------|------|-----------|--------------|
| **L1** | Ward Admin | L1 issues in their ward | — |
| **L2** | District Admin | L1 + L2 issues | Promote L1 admins, delete issues |
| **L3** | City Admin | All issues | Promote anyone, full control |

- 🎚️ **Level-aware dashboard** — each admin only sees what's in their jurisdiction
- ✅ **Status updates** + internal comments visible to citizens
- 🔧 **Issue assignment** to specific admins
- ⏱️ **Auto-escalation cron** — idle issues escalate automatically
  - Ward → District after 48 h idle (Critical issues escalate at 0.5× → 24 h)
  - District → City after 72 h idle
- 👥 **Team management panel** — promote/demote users from the dashboard

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Frontend
| Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **React 19** + Vite | UI framework + dev server with `/api` proxy |
| **React Router v6** | Client-side routing |
| **Framer Motion** | Animations |
| **Leaflet** + React-Leaflet | Interactive maps |
| **Context API** | Global state — `AuthContext`, `IssueContext` |
| **Custom hooks** | `useIssueForm` encapsulates all form logic |
| **Vercel** | Hosting + CDN |

### Backend
| Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **Node.js** + **Express** | REST API server |
| **MongoDB** + **Mongoose** | Database + ODM |
| **bcryptjs** | Password hashing |
| **jsonwebtoken** | JWT authentication |
| **setInterval cron** | Auto-escalation background job |
| **Render** | Hosting |

### Architecture
```
Frontend (MVC-inspired)
├── pages/       → Controllers  (smart, read context, call hooks)
├── components/  → Views        (pure UI — props in, JSX out, no API calls)
├── context/     → Global state (AuthContext, IssueContext)
├── hooks/       → Reusable logic
└── services/    → API layer    (all fetch() calls isolated here)
```

