## ⚡ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- Free [MongoDB Atlas](https://cloud.mongodb.com) account

### 1 — Clone
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/civicconnect.git
cd civicconnect
```

### 2 — Backend
```bash
cd Backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `Backend/.env` — fill in **two things only**:
```env
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<pass>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/civicconnect?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=any_random_string_min_32_characters
```

```bash
npm run dev
# Server running on http://localhost:5000 🚀
# MongoDB Connected ✅
```

### 3 — Frontend
```bash
cd ../Frontend
npm install
npm run dev
# http://localhost:5173
```

> ✅ No URL configuration needed. The Vite proxy forwards all `/api/*` calls to the backend automatically — works on every machine out of the box.

### 4 — Create your first admin

1. Sign up at `http://localhost:5173`
2. Open **MongoDB Atlas** → Collections → `users` → find your document → Edit:
```json
{
  "role": "admin",
  "adminLevel": 3,
  "city": "Your City"
}
```
3. Log out and log back in → you're now **City Admin (L3)**

