## 🗺️ API Reference

### Auth — `/api/auth`

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|--------|----------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/register` | — | Create citizen account |
| POST | `/login` | — | Returns JWT token |
| GET | `/me` | 🔒 User | Current user profile |
| PATCH | `/promote` | 🔑 L2+ | Promote user to admin |
| PATCH | `/demote` | 🔑 L2+ | Demote admin to citizen |
| GET | `/admins` | 🔑 L1+ | List all admins |

### Issues — `/api/issues`

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|--------|----------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/` | — | All issues — filter + paginate |
| GET | `/:id` | — | Single issue (full details) |
| POST | `/` | 🔒 User | Create issue |
| PATCH | `/:id/status` | 🔑 L1+ | Update status + add comment |
| PATCH | `/:id/assign` | 🔑 L1+ | Assign to admin |
| PATCH | `/:id/priority` | 🔑 L1+ | Manual priority override |
| POST | `/:id/escalate` | 🔑 L1+ | Escalate with reason |
| POST | `/:id/upvote` | 🔒 User | Toggle upvote (auto-upgrades priority) |
| POST | `/:id/comment` | 🔒 User | Add comment |
| DELETE | `/:id` | 🔑 L2+ | Delete issue |
| DELETE | `/` | 🔑 L2+ | Delete all issues |

**Filter params for `GET /api/issues`:**
```
?category=Roads & Potholes   # any of the 15 categories
&status=Pending               # Pending | In Progress | Resolved | Escalated
&priority=High                # Low | Medium | High | Critical
&level=1                      # 1 | 2 | 3
&page=1
&limit=20
```

---

## 🔺 Auto-Escalation Logic

```
Issue created
  → currentLevel: 1 (Ward)
  → priority: Low

Community upvotes:
  10 votes  → priority: Medium  (idle threshold × 1.0 multiplier)
  25 votes  → priority: High    (idle threshold × 0.75 — escalates faster)
  50 votes  → priority: Critical (idle threshold × 0.5 — escalates fastest)

Escalation cron (runs every 60 min):
  L1 idle 48h  → currentLevel: 2, status: Escalated, assignedTo: null
  L2 idle 72h  → currentLevel: 3, status: Escalated, assignedTo: null
  L3           → no further escalation — City Admin must act
```

All thresholds are configurable in `Backend/.env`.

